                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> Josephine Langhorn was the half-sister of my wife—I have had constant correspondence with her till the 22nd of March—she was then at New York—here is a letter her mother had from her, and I received it from her mother's hand—I know it to be her writing—she here signs her name "Josephine Mortimer"—here is not any allusion to her being married—it is dated March the 23rd, the post-mark at New York is March 29, and the London post-mark is the 15th of April—I have a letter from the prisoner—I do not know his writing, but it has his name, and was posted from Newgate.</p>
